Title: [REPEAT 1] Developing serverless .NET Core on AWS
Description: In this demonstration-heavy session, we highlight the latest techniques, tools, and libraries for developing with .NET Core on AWS. The focus is on serverless applications with AWS Lambda and AWS Fargate, but the techniques are broadly relevant. Learn about useful features and best practices for authoring serverless applications, including debugging locally from the IDE and in production, as well as how to set up your CI/CD workflow from the start.

Title: The Badly Behaved Prime (with James Maynard) - Numberphile Podcast
Description:
James Maynard is making waves in the world of prime numbers - we spoke to him in his office at Oxford University.

James is appointed a professor - https://www.maths.ox.ac.uk/node/26989

And wins the Cole Prize - http://www.ams.org/tools/news?news_id=5602

James discusses the Twin Prime Conjecture - Numberphile video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QKHKD8bRAro

Title: ASP.NET Blog | Improvements in .NET Core 3.0 for troubleshooting and monitoring distributed apps
Description:
Post was authored by Sergey Kanzhelev. Thank you David Fowler and Richard Lander for reviews.
Introduction
Operating distributed apps is hard. Distributed apps typically consists of multiple components. These components may be owned and operated by different teams. Every interaction with an app results in distributed trace of code executions across many components.
